For anyone wanting to do the distance trick, it's much easier and quicker to divide the distance to your destination by your speed first.  That gives you a decimal (in the example given, that decimal would be about .45 or so).  You can probably estimate the time from that (.45 of an hour is about 27 minutes), or you can just multiply that decimal by 60.  Even though you're doing the same math, I find it easier to rearrange into these steps than trying to multiply two larger numbers together.

I just wanted to say i appreciate all of the vids released by tkor!!  Watching this one tho, there is a faster way to cool the drinks with just ice and salt!  You submerge the can in the ice, pour salt on top to cool the ice more, THEN spin the can in the ice!  Best if you have the can on it's side when u spin it inside the ice.  The reason of the spin: as the can starts to cool down, the condensation on the can prevents the contents from cooling quickly (like a natural insulator).  By spinning the can, it keeps the condensation in motion from the can thus cooling the contents a lot quicker.  You will be amazed that it could get it ice cold with ice+salt+spin in about 30-50 seconds
